{
  "texts": [
    "The theoretical foundation of SAC models was explored using normalized variables and weight matrices 116.",
    "A more efficient and sensitive procedure for computing SAC was also proposed, known as the Skiena A algorithm and statistic.",
    "This algorithm is much faster than the computations for either Moran's I or Geary's C 117.",
    "Ongoing discussions and analyses are also examining issues such as the scale effects of SAC measurement, which are contributing to a deeper understanding of SAC and its applications in different domains 118, 119.",
    "The most common ways to eliminate the influence of SAC in the data on the prediction quality include proper sampling design, careful feature selection method, model selection, and spatial cross-validation, which we discuss further."
  ]
}